The paper proposes a process calculus for studying the behavioural theory of interactions in collective-adaptive systems, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of Labeled Transition Systems and bisimilarity also suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the study of system descriptions at different levels of abstraction suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
